5:
Peace and quiet... Finally feels like
we're getting a well deserved rest.
8:
I could do with more days like this
one... Yesterday was complete
chaos.
12:
Naska's behaving today, so we're
probably safe for now.
25: Yeah, I am. Who are you?
27:
We are Double Up—twins of fiery
passion, gamblers extraordinaire!
30: By the way, I'm the younger one.
34: Not like we can tell the difference...
41:
Do you even need to ask? When
gamblers meet, there can only be
one outcome!
43:
Naska Etrange, gambler of legend!
Today is the day we defeat you and
carve out our own legacy!
46:
...What exactly have you done in this
world to be hailed as a legend?
50:
You could say I've had a colorful
career.
All right, I'll throw down if you're
willing.
54:
Whoa, let's not go rushing into
things here. You sure you should be
taking the BOTH of them on at once?
58:
Why not? Seems fun. Stop fussin'
over her, Alk.
61:
Our challenge has been accepted!
Excellent!
62:
We will face off with a
classic—blackjack. You find this
agreeable, yes?
64:
Haha, that's your angle, huh? Sure, I'll
deal.
67:
Dealers have the disadvantage in
blackjack!
68:
But she had to take that position, or
risk tarnishing her reputation!
70: Not afraid to be underhanded, huh...
73:
Silence! Every bit of prior
preparation counts for these bouts!
74:
Exactly! We racked our brains for
this perfect strategy—
76:
That's a 10 and an ace for me.
Blackjack.
81:
Eh, your strategy was on the right
track. The more times you play
blackjack, the more likely the dealer
is to lose.
83:
But you should've made it a best out
of 5 or something before we started.
That's where you messed up.
86:
I underestimated the legend... I'm
sorry, brother!
90:
Huh... You'd think they would've been
more of a challenge with the way
they swaggered around.
93:
Perhaps Naska was simply beyond
their level.
102: Sheesh, is that all you've got...
111:
Hmm, more like I'm still buzzing from
that challenge earlier.
115: Your poker face is real lousy.
121:
I just figured since we're on
vacation, I should take it a little
easy...
125:
But that sad bit of blackjack during
lunch made me crave a real throw
down even harder!
128:
So stop holding back and go
scratch that itch. Hell, take all the
crazy bets you want too.
131:
I'm here to relax with everyone, not
go running off by myself like I know
Marina would do. I can be
considerate!
138:
Anyway, it's all right. I'm having
plenty of fun just hanging out with
you guys.
141:
Fine. If that's really how you feel,
then I won't complain.
144:
Doesn't make it any less of a boring
way to pass the time though.
149: Hey, no one said you could sass me!
153:
Like you said, you're here to relax
and have fun.
156:
Fun can be whatever you want it to
be. You get to choose.
160: What the heck was that about...
163:
My poker face must really be
slipping, huh...
169:
I suppose I'll have to show my real
hand soon.
